<span id="freeTextContainer434885890348107855"><b>&quot;A collection of 300 poems from writers around the world, selected and edited by Nobel laureate Czeslaw Milosz</b> Czesław Miłosz&apos;s <i>A Book of Luminous Things</i>—his personal selection of poems from the past and present—is a testament to the stunning varieties of human experience, offered up so that we may see the myriad ways that experience can be shared in words and images. Miło</span>
  <span id="freeText434885890348107855" style="display:none"><b>"A collection of 300 poems from writers around the world, selected and edited by Nobel laureate Czeslaw Milosz</b> Czesław Miłosz's <i>A Book of Luminous Things</i>—his personal selection of poems from the past and present—is a testament to the stunning varieties of human experience, offered up so that we may see the myriad ways that experience can be shared in words and images. Miłosz provides a preface to each of these poems, divided into thematic (and often beguiling) sections, such as “Travel,” “History,” and “The Secret of a Thing,” that make the reading as instructional as it is inspirational and remind us how powerfully poetry can touch our minds and hearts. "<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="434885890348107855" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

