<div id="review_3342365183" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3342365183" />
    <a title="Robert Hudder" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12148134-robert-hudder"><img alt="Robert Hudder" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3342365183?book_show_action=true">May 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robert Hudder" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robert Hudder" href="/user/show/12148134-robert-hudder">Robert Hudder</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3342365183" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16090396887739932366">Sometimes, poetry seems to try to hard and not have any connection. Whether slam that requests that you witness, or maybe some type of classical poetry that tries to get at Truth. <br/><br/>These aren&apos;t those poems. This collection from all over the place at different times feels fresh. The focus is on a being more present and real, for a lack of a better term. These are poems about objects and things. Less flower and description and more sparse and hard. <br/><br/>There are some surprising poems here. Some poets t</span>
  <span id="freeText16090396887739932366" style="display:none">Sometimes, poetry seems to try to hard and not have any connection. Whether slam that requests that you witness, or maybe some type of classical poetry that tries to get at Truth. <br /><br />These aren't those poems. This collection from all over the place at different times feels fresh. The focus is on a being more present and real, for a lack of a better term. These are poems about objects and things. Less flower and description and more sparse and hard. <br /><br />There are some surprising poems here. Some poets that you expect are here but with poems that you don't. I really enjoyed that. I had to pay better attention. The style didn't force meaning or feel like a presentation. There were no gilded ideas. Just poems about getting drunk, getting sober and looking at things. That is all. And it is good.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16090396887739932366" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


